1
00:01:42,041 --> 00:01:43,375
[PLISETSKY FANGIRLS squealing]

2
00:01:43,458 --> 00:01:44,541
[FANGIRL 8A]
Look!

3
00:01:44,625 --> 00:01:45,333
[FANGIRL 8B]
Yakov and his team are here!

4
00:01:45,416 --> 00:01:47,000
[FANGIRL 8C]
Yurochka!

5
00:01:47,083 --> 00:01:48,083
[FANGIRL 8D]
Yuri!

6
00:01:48,166 --> 00:01:49,708
Mira, watch my luggage.

7
00:01:49,791 --> 00:01:51,458
Huh?

8
00:01:51,541 --> 00:01:52,833
Hey, Coach Yakov.

9
00:01:52,916 --> 00:01:54,375
Yuri ran off somewhere.

10
00:01:54,458 --> 00:01:55,791
Da.

11
00:01:55,875 --> 00:01:58,916
He has family here in Moscow.
They're picking him up.

12
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,458
[PLISETSKY]
My name is Yuri Plisetski.

13
00:02:01,541 --> 00:02:03,708
My goal is to be named
the top skater in the world

14
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:05,583
in my first senior season.

15
00:02:05,666 --> 00:02:08,875
I am the unbeatable
Ice Tiger of Russia.

16
00:02:08,958 --> 00:02:11,000
Oh, Yuri!

17
00:02:11,083 --> 00:02:12,375
Grandpa!

18
00:02:12,458 --> 00:02:13,791
[crack]

19
00:02:13,875 --> 00:02:14,833
[GRANDPA PLISETSKY groans]

20
00:02:14,916 --> 00:02:15,708
[PLISETSKY]
I'm sorry, I'm sorry!

21
00:02:15,791 --> 00:02:17,833
I forgot about your bad back!

22
00:02:17,916 --> 00:02:22,666
[GRANDPA PLISETSKY] I made
my pirozhkis for you--eat!

23
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:25,916
Hey, Grandpa. Ever try
a pork cutlet bowl?

24
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,125
[GRANDPA PLISETSKY]
What's that?

25
00:02:27,208 --> 00:02:28,666
[PLISETSKY]
Something I had back in Japan.

26
00:02:28,750 --> 00:02:30,583
They're really good.

27
00:02:30,666 --> 00:02:33,083
So, my pirozhkis aren't
good enough for you now?

28
00:02:33,166 --> 00:02:35,666
No! Sorry! That's
not what I meant!

29
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:37,583
[RADIO HOST 8A] Russian
national hero Victor Nikiforov

30
00:02:37,666 --> 00:02:40,375
has returned home for the Figure
Skating Grand Prix series.

31
00:02:40,458 --> 00:02:43,125
This year, he'll be coaching
rather than competing.

32
00:02:44,458 --> 00:02:46,958
[YURI]
"Yuri vs. Yuri. The Horror!!

33
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:49,666
Rostelecom Cup, Short Program."

34
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:50,791
[REPORTER 8A]
How do you feel about

35
00:02:50,875 --> 00:02:52,208
coming back to Russia?

36
00:02:52,291 --> 00:02:54,083
[REPORTER 8B]
When will you return to skating?

37
00:02:54,166 --> 00:02:55,916
Until the Grand Prix
Final is done,

38
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,083
I won't comment
on any future plans.

39
00:02:58,166 --> 00:03:01,333
Right now, I see a lot of
potential in Yuri Katsuki.

40
00:03:01,416 --> 00:03:02,833
I think the focus
should be on him

41
00:03:02,916 --> 00:03:04,541
during the Rostelecom Cup.

42
00:03:04,625 --> 00:03:06,583
[PLISETSKY]
I'm in it, too, stupid.

43
00:03:06,666 --> 00:03:08,916
You're well-known as a skater
who likes a challenge.

44
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,958
Wouldn't you rather face
a man of Yuri's charisma

45
00:03:11,041 --> 00:03:13,208
as a fellow competitor?

46
00:03:13,291 --> 00:03:14,750
[PLISETSKY]
Hm.

47
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:16,750
Hey! It's Yurio!

48
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:19,250
[REPORTER 8D]
Yuri Plisetsky!

49
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:21,625
Did you all check out
the short program I designed?

50
00:03:21,708 --> 00:03:23,500
For Yurio?

51
00:03:25,208 --> 00:03:28,250
You're not Russia's
top skater anymore, Victor.

52
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:30,958
I'm the star of this event.

53
00:03:34,958 --> 00:03:37,500
[YURI] Oh, it's
Seung Gil Lee from Korea.

54
00:03:37,583 --> 00:03:39,458
I was on friendly terms
with the other skaters

55
00:03:39,541 --> 00:03:43,083
at the Cup of China.
But here, not so much.

56
00:03:43,166 --> 00:03:44,458
[MICHELE] You want to
date my little sister,

57
00:03:44,541 --> 00:03:46,291
you better be ready
to go through me.

58
00:03:46,375 --> 00:03:47,916
[laughs] Take it easy.

59
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,666
Mickey! Calm down.

60
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:51,166
We were just going
out to grab a bite.

61
00:03:51,250 --> 00:03:52,833
[MICHELE]
My sister's out of your league!

62
00:03:52,916 --> 00:03:55,666
You don't deserve to eat
at the same table as her!

63
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:58,083
Hey, Yuri!

64
00:03:58,166 --> 00:04:00,291
We're just grabbing some food.
Would you like to come?

65
00:04:00,375 --> 00:04:00,875
[SEUNG GIL]
No.

66
00:04:00,958 --> 00:04:02,208
Jeez.

67
00:04:02,291 --> 00:04:03,666
If you don't want to go,
maybe you could find a way

68
00:04:03,750 --> 00:04:07,333
to say that without being
a total jerk about it.

69
00:04:07,416 --> 00:04:09,208
I get no benefit
from being nice to you,

70
00:04:09,291 --> 00:04:10,250
so why bother?

71
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:11,458
--[SARA] Seriously?
--How dare you

72
00:04:11,541 --> 00:04:12,666
--[SARA] Seriously?
--speak that way to her?

73
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:13,666
I'll rip your eyeballs out,
you little runt!

74
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:15,125
I mean it! Get over here!

75
00:04:15,208 --> 00:04:16,166
[SEUNG GIL]
You're in my way.

76
00:04:16,250 --> 00:04:18,041
[MICHELE]
What?!

77
00:04:18,125 --> 00:04:18,916
[gasps]

78
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,750
Why are you sneaking around?

79
00:04:20,833 --> 00:04:23,291
[YURI] Hey, Yurio.
Good to see you again.

80
00:04:27,208 --> 00:04:28,750
I know both of us can't win,

81
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:30,291
but I'm sure we'll
both skate well.

82
00:04:30,375 --> 00:04:31,666
<i>Niet</i> .

83
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:33,958
You will suffer a miserable
defeat here in Moscow.

84
00:04:34,041 --> 00:04:37,166
Then you will go back home
and Victor will stay in Russia.

85
00:04:37,250 --> 00:04:38,916
[YURI]
What if he's right?

86
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,333
If I don't rank higher
than fourth here,

87
00:04:41,416 --> 00:04:43,791
I won't advance to
the Grand Prix final.

88
00:04:43,875 --> 00:04:48,208
And if I don't,
what will Victor do then?

89
00:04:48,291 --> 00:04:49,791
[NAOHIKO]
The Men's singles short program

90
00:04:49,875 --> 00:04:52,291
is about to start
here in Moscow.

91
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:54,958
Here's where the rankings stand
after the series' fifth event,

92
00:04:55,041 --> 00:04:58,208
Trophée de France.


93
00:04:58,291 --> 00:04:59,458
Only the top
six skaters

94
00:04:59,541 --> 00:05:00,375
will advance to

95
00:05:00,458 --> 00:05:02,541
the Grand Prix Final.

96
00:05:02,625 --> 00:05:05,458
There are just two
confirmed qualifiers so far.

97
00:05:05,541 --> 00:05:07,958
Otabek Altin of Kazakhstan,
who placed second

98
00:05:08,041 --> 00:05:10,791
in Skate America and
won the NHK Trophy.

99
00:05:10,875 --> 00:05:12,833
And Christophe Giacometti,
who placed third

100
00:05:12,916 --> 00:05:15,583
at the Cup of China and first
at the Trophée de France.

101
00:05:15,666 --> 00:05:16,500
And now the skaters

102
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:18,875
fighting for the
last four spots.

103
00:05:18,958 --> 00:05:21,166
Canada's Jean-Jaques Leroy,
the lead contender

104
00:05:21,250 --> 00:05:24,041
after winning on his home
turf at Skate Canada.

105
00:05:24,125 --> 00:05:25,958
Seung Gil Lee
of Korea, a newcomer

106
00:05:26,041 --> 00:05:27,791
to the Grand Prix Series
who placed second

107
00:05:27,875 --> 00:05:29,541
at the NHK Trophy.

108
00:05:29,625 --> 00:05:32,208
Michele Crispino of Italy,
here with his sister Sara,

109
00:05:32,291 --> 00:05:34,791
after placing third
in the NHK Trophy.

110
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:36,583
Emil Nekola, from the
Czech Republic,

111
00:05:36,666 --> 00:05:39,125
who took third at Skate Canada.

112
00:05:39,208 --> 00:05:40,666
Russia's own Yuri Plisetsky,

113
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:42,375
who made a brilliant
senior debut,

114
00:05:42,458 --> 00:05:44,708
finishing second
at Skate Canada.

115
00:05:44,791 --> 00:05:46,666
And finally,
Japan's Yuri Katsuki,

116
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:48,625
who placed second
at the Cup of China.

117
00:05:48,708 --> 00:05:50,750
He will be skating
in the final group.

118
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:53,041
The Rostelecom Cup results
will also determine

119
00:05:53,125 --> 00:05:54,708
whether Thailand's
Phichit Chulanont

120
00:05:54,791 --> 00:05:56,458
will advance to the Final.

121
00:05:59,250 --> 00:06:01,083
Damn it, the livestream
keeps cutting out.

122
00:06:01,166 --> 00:06:02,958
I knew I should've
gone to Russia!

123
00:06:03,041 --> 00:06:04,375
That's it, you three,
get to bed!

124
00:06:04,458 --> 00:06:05,791
--No You can't make us!
--[LUTZ] We wanna watch it live!

125
00:06:05,875 --> 00:06:07,375
--[LOOP] Please, Mom!
--[LUTZ] We wanna watch it live!

126
00:06:07,458 --> 00:06:10,833
[MOROOKA] All right, Group One's
six-minute warm-up has ended.

127
00:06:10,916 --> 00:06:12,833
[SEUNG GIL'S COACH] Seung Gil,
are you listening to me?

128
00:06:12,916 --> 00:06:14,833
Everything you do
is for PyeongChang.

129
00:06:14,916 --> 00:06:16,875
That's where your focus
needs to be. Seung Gil!

130
00:06:16,958 --> 00:06:19,083
[MOROOKA] Seung Gil Lee
of Korea, age 20.

131
00:06:19,166 --> 00:06:21,083
In his first event,
the NHK Trophy,

132
00:06:21,166 --> 00:06:22,791
he thrilled the crowd
with his short program

133
00:06:22,875 --> 00:06:24,958
skated to this
piece, "Almavivo."

134
00:06:25,041 --> 00:06:28,583
["Almavivo" plays]

135
00:06:28,666 --> 00:06:30,166
[MOROOKA]
His first jump will be a quad.

136
00:06:30,250 --> 00:06:31,708
He is the only
skater in the world

137
00:06:31,791 --> 00:06:34,208
to have landed this
jump in competition.

138
00:06:34,291 --> 00:06:35,708
A quadruple loop!

139
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:38,208
Incredible!

140
00:06:38,291 --> 00:06:41,000
[SEUNG GIL]
The base value is 12.0.

141
00:06:41,083 --> 00:06:42,458
[MOROOKA] Seung Gil Lee
has selected "greed"

142
00:06:42,541 --> 00:06:45,833
as his theme for this season.

143
00:06:45,916 --> 00:06:47,666
He hopes to gain an edge
in the competition

144
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:51,333
by amping up the sex appeal
in his performance.

145
00:06:51,416 --> 00:06:53,250
Crap. He's doing that, too?

146
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:54,791
Sex appeal inflation!

147
00:06:54,875 --> 00:06:55,791
[LOOP]
There is way...

148
00:06:55,875 --> 00:06:56,541
[LUTZ]
...too much...

149
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:57,541
[AXEL]
...sex appeal!

150
00:06:57,625 --> 00:06:58,958
[AUDIENCE applauding]

151
00:06:59,041 --> 00:07:01,291
[MOROOKA] Seung Gil always
seeks to break new ground.

152
00:07:01,375 --> 00:07:04,000
In addition to the exceptionally
difficult quadruple loop,

153
00:07:04,083 --> 00:07:07,375
he also requested to skate
a mambo for his short program.

154
00:07:09,583 --> 00:07:10,458
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple axel.

155
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:11,750
[MOROOKA]
Oh, he takes a fall!

156
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:12,875
[SEUNG GIL]
Enough rotation.

157
00:07:12,958 --> 00:07:15,583
Second-half jump
gets a 1.1 multiplier.

158
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:19,416
So, 9.35 with a
deduction of one.

159
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:21,500
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
Triple Lutz, triple toe loop!

160
00:07:21,583 --> 00:07:23,041
[MOROOKA]
No mistakes there!

161
00:07:23,125 --> 00:07:25,291
[SEUNG GIL] Eleven point one one
points, with the multiplier.

162
00:07:25,375 --> 00:07:27,291
Now the last element,
a step sequence.

163
00:07:27,375 --> 00:07:29,041
[MOROOKA]
What a passionate step sequence!

164
00:07:29,125 --> 00:07:31,708
The polish in his execution
should be well received

165
00:07:31,791 --> 00:07:33,041
by the judges.

166
00:07:45,208 --> 00:07:47,541
Zero expression,
but his steps are killer.

167
00:07:47,625 --> 00:07:49,666
He's even better than
at the NHK Trophy.

168
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:50,791
[LOOP]
Totally!

169
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:56,625
[AUDIENCE cheers]

170
00:07:56,708 --> 00:07:59,500
[EMIL] Oh! That'll be
a hard act to follow, ya?

171
00:07:59,583 --> 00:08:01,083
--I've never seen you get
--[SARA] I could devour him!

172
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:03,041
nervous before, and I don't
think you're going to start now.

173
00:08:03,125 --> 00:08:04,250
You know, you're right.

174
00:08:04,333 --> 00:08:06,083
We'll all make it to Barcelona!

175
00:08:06,166 --> 00:08:10,625
[MOROOKA] Seung Gil Lee
scores 91.83, a personal best.


176
00:08:10,708 --> 00:08:12,625
He's currently in first place.


177
00:08:12,708 --> 00:08:16,916
Next up is Emil Nekola
of the Czech Republic, age 18.

178
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,291
[EMIL]
Hm!

179
00:08:18,375 --> 00:08:20,750
I don't let crowd's response
affect my performance.

180
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:22,416
--[AUDIENCE cheers]
--Huh?

181
00:08:24,083 --> 00:08:25,833
[MICHELE] There's no denying
that guy can jump,

182
00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:27,833
but his performance
is lackluster.

183
00:08:27,916 --> 00:08:29,833
<i>Si</i> .

184
00:08:29,916 --> 00:08:31,541
[SARA]
Once Mickey's done,

185
00:08:31,625 --> 00:08:33,708
it'll almost be time
for Group Two.

186
00:08:33,791 --> 00:08:34,916
Did you hear that, Yuri?

187
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,166
Emil landed a quadruple
loop, as well.

188
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:39,250
We should clap for him, eh?

189
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:41,208
Oh. Sorry, I didn't catch that.

190
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:43,666
[JEAN-JACQUES] You did the same
jump at last year's exhibition,

191
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:46,125
didn't you, Victor?
I'd love to see that again.

192
00:08:46,208 --> 00:08:47,250
I don't recall.

193
00:08:47,333 --> 00:08:48,458
Aw!

194
00:08:48,541 --> 00:08:51,250
[MOROOKA]
Emil Nekola's score is 82.43.


195
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:53,541
That means he is currently
in second place.

196
00:08:53,625 --> 00:08:56,291
Hey, Mickey, let's
see you beat that!

197
00:08:56,375 --> 00:08:57,583
Mickey! Sara! Hey!

198
00:08:57,666 --> 00:08:59,833
[MOROOKA] Next up is
Michele Crispino of Italy.

199
00:08:59,916 --> 00:09:02,208
His sister Sara
is here to support him.

200
00:09:04,333 --> 00:09:06,166
[MOROOKA]
He is skating to "L'Homme Armé"

201
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:09,250
from the movie
<i>Destiny of Knights</i> .

202
00:09:09,333 --> 00:09:10,416
[MICHELE]
Watch me, Sara!

203
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:12,750
I am your knight
in shining armor!

204
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:17,791
["L'Homme Armé" playing]

205
00:09:25,125 --> 00:09:25,875
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple axel.

206
00:09:25,958 --> 00:09:27,541
Bravo!

207
00:09:27,625 --> 00:09:29,208
[MICHELE] I've defeated
every man who has tried

208
00:09:29,291 --> 00:09:31,166
to take Sara from my side.

209
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:32,791
She and I will be
together forever,

210
00:09:32,875 --> 00:09:35,083
supporting each other
on and off the ice.

211
00:09:35,166 --> 00:09:37,708
No one could love
her more than I do!

212
00:09:37,791 --> 00:09:38,583
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A quad Sal.

213
00:09:38,666 --> 00:09:39,375
[MOROOKA]
Ah, he fell!

214
00:09:39,458 --> 00:09:41,166
[gasps]

215
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:43,833
[MICHELE] Sara, your own
short program is coming up.

216
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:46,291
I don't want you
to go into it worried.

217
00:09:46,375 --> 00:09:49,916
As your older brother and a man,
it's my duty to protect you.

218
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:53,041
Unlike physical love, the love
of a brother is unconditional.

219
00:09:53,125 --> 00:09:55,291
I will always be there for you!

220
00:09:55,375 --> 00:09:56,625
[MOROOKA]
Next up is a triple Lutz,

221
00:09:56,708 --> 00:09:59,458
triple toe loop combination.

222
00:09:59,541 --> 00:10:00,166
[gasps]

223
00:10:00,250 --> 00:10:01,625
[SARA]
Is he...?

224
00:10:03,791 --> 00:10:06,583
[MOROOKA] He turned it into
a triple Lutz, triple loop!

225
00:10:06,666 --> 00:10:09,500
A very high-difficulty
combination.

226
00:10:09,583 --> 00:10:10,875
Among active skaters,

227
00:10:10,958 --> 00:10:14,291
the only one to even attempt
it is his sister, Sara.

228
00:10:14,375 --> 00:10:16,833
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
Well, that sure was a surprise!

229
00:10:16,916 --> 00:10:18,333
[MICHELE]
Sara.

230
00:10:18,416 --> 00:10:21,125
I'm sure you'll land that
combination, just like I did.

231
00:10:21,208 --> 00:10:24,666
Don't worry. We will
always be together.

232
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:27,000
[AUDIENCE cheers]

233
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:33,791
[AUDIENCE cheers]

234
00:10:36,416 --> 00:10:39,750
[SARA] He has to find a way
to skate without me by his side.

235
00:10:39,833 --> 00:10:40,833
[MICHELE]
Sara!

236
00:10:40,916 --> 00:10:42,375
[SARA]
Well done!

237
00:10:42,458 --> 00:10:45,666
[SARA] If something doesn't
change, it will ruin both of us.

238
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:57,708
[MOROOKA] Michele Crispino's
score is 89.65.


239
00:10:57,791 --> 00:10:59,833
He is currently in second place.


240
00:11:02,208 --> 00:11:05,958
Grandpa, where are you?

241
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,458
[panting]

242
00:11:16,416 --> 00:11:17,666
[MINAKO]
Oh, come on!

243
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:19,000
Are you kidding me, here?

244
00:11:19,083 --> 00:11:21,833
Why can't they just show
the damn thing on live TV?

245
00:11:23,041 --> 00:11:26,375
[MINAKO] There we go!
Wow, he's already up?

246
00:11:26,458 --> 00:11:28,208
[ALL]
Go get 'em, Yuri!

247
00:11:29,250 --> 00:11:31,500
I thought I told you
three to go to bed!

248
00:11:31,583 --> 00:11:33,375
[MOROOKA] Yuri Katsuki
channeled the power of love

249
00:11:33,458 --> 00:11:35,500
to take second
at the Cup of China.

250
00:11:35,583 --> 00:11:38,208
I wonder what he's got
up his sleeve today.

251
00:11:38,291 --> 00:11:39,458
[VICTOR]
Ah--

252
00:11:40,916 --> 00:11:44,583
[YURI] The performance has
already started, Victor.

253
00:11:44,666 --> 00:11:46,541
[VICTOR]
I know it has.

254
00:11:46,625 --> 00:11:48,166
I'm going to go out there,

255
00:11:48,250 --> 00:11:51,000
and I'm going to show my love
to the whole of Russia.

256
00:11:51,083 --> 00:11:53,750
[ANNOUNCER 8B] The next skater,
representing Japan,

257
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:55,416
Yuri Katsuki!

258
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:57,125
[YURI]
That was so embarrassing.

259
00:11:57,208 --> 00:12:00,916
I can't let the crowd intimidate
me in enemy territory.

260
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,166
I have to intimidate them.

261
00:12:03,250 --> 00:12:08,208
["On Love: Eros" plays]

262
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,208
[JUDGES gasp]

263
00:12:12,291 --> 00:12:13,625
["On Love: Eros" continues]

264
00:12:13,708 --> 00:12:16,375
[MOROOKA]
Japan's Yuri Katsuki, age 23,

265
00:12:16,458 --> 00:12:19,125
skating to "On Love: Eros."

266
00:12:19,208 --> 00:12:20,583
He's been consistently beating

267
00:12:20,666 --> 00:12:22,583
his short program
personal bests.

268
00:12:22,666 --> 00:12:24,541
He will need to finish
fourth or higher here

269
00:12:24,625 --> 00:12:26,666
to advance to the
Grand Prix Final.

270
00:12:28,375 --> 00:12:30,958
[YURI] If I don't do well enough
at the Rostelecom Cup,

271
00:12:31,041 --> 00:12:33,208
this may be the last time
I skate this program

272
00:12:33,291 --> 00:12:35,666
with Victor as my coach.

273
00:12:35,750 --> 00:12:37,250
I don't know how many
people in the world

274
00:12:37,333 --> 00:12:40,875
want me to win. Probably
no one here in Russia.

275
00:12:40,958 --> 00:12:43,291
It's not a very
comforting thought.

276
00:12:43,375 --> 00:12:47,041
But that doesn't matter.
I can't let it stop me.

277
00:12:47,125 --> 00:12:48,875
[VICTOR]
Yuri seems to be more motivated

278
00:12:48,958 --> 00:12:50,791
competing further from home.

279
00:12:50,875 --> 00:12:53,333
Whatever the reason,
he's in top form.

280
00:13:14,208 --> 00:13:17,166
[AUDIENCE cheers]

281
00:13:19,416 --> 00:13:21,250
[MOROOKA] His first planned
jump is a triple axel

282
00:13:21,333 --> 00:13:22,833
from a spread eagle.

283
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:24,833
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple axel.

284
00:13:24,916 --> 00:13:26,291
[MOROOKA]
Very clean!

285
00:13:33,541 --> 00:13:34,916
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A quadruple Salchow.

286
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:37,375
Yuri! That was amazing!

287
00:13:51,125 --> 00:13:53,375
[ANNOUNCER 8A] Quadruple
toe loop, triple toe loop.

288
00:13:53,458 --> 00:13:55,416
[MOROOKA] He nailed the
jump combination, too!

289
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:58,625
[PLISETSKY]
His program has come a long way

290
00:13:58,708 --> 00:14:01,083
since the "Hot Springs
on Ice" event.

291
00:14:05,125 --> 00:14:10,083
[AUDIENCE cheers]

292
00:14:11,541 --> 00:14:12,791
[AUDIENCE cheers]

293
00:14:12,875 --> 00:14:14,250
[MOROOKA] Another flawless
performance on the heels

294
00:14:14,333 --> 00:14:17,500
of his last short program
at the Cup of China!

295
00:14:17,583 --> 00:14:20,166
It sounds like the crowd
is impressed, too!

296
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:21,333
Yuri!

297
00:14:21,416 --> 00:14:22,083
[panting]

298
00:14:22,166 --> 00:14:23,208
[YURI]
All right.

299
00:14:23,291 --> 00:14:25,458
It looks like I got
my message across.

300
00:14:25,541 --> 00:14:26,708
[PLISETSKY]
Damn it.

301
00:14:26,791 --> 00:14:28,125
I thought, with Grandpa
here, I would be able

302
00:14:28,208 --> 00:14:31,000
to skate agape perfectly.

303
00:14:31,083 --> 00:14:33,333
Yuri! That was perfec--

304
00:14:34,958 --> 00:14:36,250
Huh?

305
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:37,916
[YURI gasps]

306
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:44,875
Out of my way, piggy.

307
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:51,666
Well. I think he's
found... his agape.

308
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,500
[BOTH]
Finally!

309
00:14:53,583 --> 00:14:54,291
Yurochka!

310
00:14:54,375 --> 00:14:56,208
We love you!

311
00:14:57,291 --> 00:14:58,625
Stay calm.

312
00:14:58,708 --> 00:15:01,208
The crowd expects a lot,
but don't let them rattle you.

313
00:15:01,291 --> 00:15:03,916
[LILIA] All the work you did
in practice won't betray you.

314
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,625
[muffled] Have confidence,
like any other...

315
00:15:05,708 --> 00:15:09,666
[PLISETSKY] That's weird.
Everything sounds fuzzy.

316
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:14,000
Calm down, calm down.

317
00:15:14,083 --> 00:15:15,208
--[AUDIENCE cheering]
--[PLISETSKY gasps]

318
00:15:15,291 --> 00:15:16,375
[YURI]

319
00:15:16,458 --> 00:15:17,583
[MOROOKA]
One oh nine point nine seven!

320
00:15:17,666 --> 00:15:19,791
He beat his personal best again!

321
00:15:19,875 --> 00:15:22,000
That puts him in first place!

322
00:15:24,541 --> 00:15:26,583
[MOROOKA] Nikiforov is
so overcome with pride,

323
00:15:26,666 --> 00:15:28,333
he kisses Katsuki's skate.

324
00:15:28,416 --> 00:15:29,625
Now there's a devoted coach!

325
00:15:29,708 --> 00:15:31,583
<i>Davai</i> ! Yurio!

326
00:15:31,666 --> 00:15:32,750
Huh?

327
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:33,625
[YURI]

328
00:15:33,708 --> 00:15:35,333
Skate well! <i>Ganbate</i> !

329
00:15:35,416 --> 00:15:38,208
[PLISETSKY growls]

330
00:15:38,291 --> 00:15:40,750
[ANNOUNCER 8B] The next skater,
representing Russia,

331
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:42,458
--Yuri Plisetsky.
--Yuri!

332
00:15:42,541 --> 00:15:44,416
[MOROOKA]
The Russian skating prodigy,

333
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:46,958
Yuri Plisetsky, age 15.

334
00:15:47,041 --> 00:15:50,250
His program was choreographed
by Victor Nikiforov.

335
00:15:52,291 --> 00:15:53,458
[PLISETSKY]
Damn it.

336
00:15:53,541 --> 00:15:56,000
I don't need you idiots
cheering me on.

337
00:15:56,083 --> 00:15:58,000
I'm not that desperate.

338
00:15:58,083 --> 00:15:59,208
["On Love: Agape" plays]

339
00:15:59,291 --> 00:16:01,750
[MOROOKA] He's skating
to "On Love: Agape,"

340
00:16:01,833 --> 00:16:03,250
a different arrangement
of the music

341
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:06,291
used in Katsuki's program
with an opposing theme.

342
00:16:06,375 --> 00:16:09,458
Crap! I'm not
feeling agape at all.

343
00:16:09,541 --> 00:16:11,750
I'm just angry!

344
00:16:11,833 --> 00:16:14,125
[MOROOKA] Here comes his
first jump, a triple axel.

345
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:17,708
[MOROOKA]
Oh! he fell!

346
00:16:17,791 --> 00:16:19,041
[PLISETSKY]
Damn it!

347
00:16:19,125 --> 00:16:21,875
I haven't missed that jump
once in the last year!

348
00:16:23,291 --> 00:16:24,750
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A flying sit spin.

349
00:16:24,833 --> 00:16:27,041
His position is quite beautiful.

350
00:16:27,125 --> 00:16:28,791
[PLISETSKY]
It's not fair!

351
00:16:28,875 --> 00:16:30,833
I've been pouring my
blood, sweat, and tears

352
00:16:30,916 --> 00:16:33,458
into this since that
humiliation in Japan.

353
00:16:36,875 --> 00:16:39,708
[PLISETSKY] I just lack
experience, that's all.

354
00:16:43,958 --> 00:16:46,833
[MOROOKA] His first quad is
coming as part of a combination.

355
00:16:49,416 --> 00:16:50,625
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
Quadruple Salchow.

356
00:16:50,708 --> 00:16:52,041
Triple toe loop.

357
00:16:52,125 --> 00:16:54,958
[MOROOKA] Fantastic execution!
Great height and flow!

358
00:16:55,041 --> 00:16:56,375
It's hard to believe
he only started doing

359
00:16:56,458 --> 00:16:59,166
that combination this season!

360
00:16:59,250 --> 00:17:02,250
Now here comes his final jump.

361
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:03,583
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A quadruple toe loop.

362
00:17:03,666 --> 00:17:04,791
[MOROOKA]
What a beautiful jump!

363
00:17:04,875 --> 00:17:06,916
He demonstrates truly
remarkable talent

364
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:09,000
for a skater of any age.

365
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:14,541
[YAKOV] Even when he
doesn't skate his best,

366
00:17:14,625 --> 00:17:17,166
he knows how to analyze
his performance mid-program

367
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:18,666
and make a comeback.

368
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:21,541
[LILIA] Beautiful.
You are a work of art.

369
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:24,541
Maintain that pride
until the very end.

370
00:17:27,375 --> 00:17:28,958
[PLISETSKY]
Keep going.

371
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:40,500
[AUDIENCE cheers]

372
00:17:40,583 --> 00:17:42,958
[MOROOKA] His supporters here
in Moscow expected a lot,

373
00:17:43,041 --> 00:17:44,875
and Yuri Plisetsky delivered it

374
00:17:44,958 --> 00:17:48,208
with an exceptional
short program!

375
00:17:48,291 --> 00:17:51,708
--[sputters]
--[PLISETSKY FANGIRLS squeal]

376
00:17:54,541 --> 00:17:56,583
Oh, I'm sorry.
Ladies first, please.

377
00:17:56,666 --> 00:17:58,000
[PLISETSKY growls]

378
00:17:58,083 --> 00:17:59,541
[PLISETSKY] I forgot there
was someone more annoying

379
00:17:59,625 --> 00:18:02,291
than those other idiots--JJ.

380
00:18:02,375 --> 00:18:04,416
Yeah, I'm feeling pretty--

381
00:18:05,583 --> 00:18:08,916
[MOROOKA]
Yuri Plisetsky's score is 98.09,


382
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,416
putting him in second place.


383
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:12,333
Yuri Katsuki remains in first.

384
00:18:12,416 --> 00:18:13,750
Today's final skater is the one

385
00:18:13,833 --> 00:18:16,333
with the most momentum going
into this competition.

386
00:18:16,416 --> 00:18:19,500
Jean-Jacques Leroy
of Canada, age 19.

387
00:18:19,583 --> 00:18:21,958
Also known as "JJ."

388
00:18:23,625 --> 00:18:25,375
[MOROOKA] He will be skating
to an original song

389
00:18:25,458 --> 00:18:29,041
composed for him:
"Theme of King JJ."

390
00:18:29,125 --> 00:18:33,791
["Theme of King JJ" plays]

391
00:18:33,875 --> 00:18:36,333
[JEAN-JACQUES] Not just anyone
can pull off a collaboration

392
00:18:36,416 --> 00:18:38,458
with a world-famous rock band.

393
00:18:38,541 --> 00:18:41,916
This is the kind of program
that only King JJ can deliver.

394
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:43,000
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
Quadruple toe loop.

395
00:18:43,083 --> 00:18:44,250
Triple toe loop.

396
00:18:44,333 --> 00:18:45,791
[MOROOKA] Some major jumps
right off the bat.

397
00:18:45,875 --> 00:18:48,208
JJ placed third at last
year's Grand Prix Final

398
00:18:48,291 --> 00:18:50,125
and took first this
year at Skate Canada,

399
00:18:50,208 --> 00:18:51,833
putting him in a solid position.

400
00:18:51,916 --> 00:18:55,500
[JEAN-JACQUES] Hmph! Hope you're
ready for another big one.

401
00:18:55,583 --> 00:18:56,583
[ANNOUNCER 8A]
A triple axel.

402
00:18:56,666 --> 00:18:57,875
[MOROOKA]
Incredible height!

403
00:18:57,958 --> 00:19:01,000
He nearly cleared the
fence with that jump.

404
00:19:01,083 --> 00:19:04,458
[JEAN-JACQUES chuckles] A lot of
top skaters load the second half

405
00:19:04,541 --> 00:19:08,000
of their programs with jumps,
but I'm different.

406
00:19:08,083 --> 00:19:09,750
I don't rely on that trick.

407
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:11,958
To me it's more important
that my skating

408
00:19:12,041 --> 00:19:17,791
and the music work together.
It's JJ Style!

409
00:19:17,875 --> 00:19:27,125
["Theme of King JJ" continues]

410
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:30,916
[JEAN-JACQUES laughs]
Let's go! Everyone, sing along!

411
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,541
[JEAN-JACQUES FANGIRLS]
♪ ...the world, JJ ♪

412
00:19:32,625 --> 00:19:34,083
♪ Just follow me ♪

413
00:19:34,166 --> 00:19:36,125
♪ I will break the walls ♪

414
00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:38,500
♪ Now look at me. ♪

415
00:19:38,583 --> 00:19:39,583
[MOROOKA]
The lyrics suggest that

416
00:19:39,666 --> 00:19:41,291
JJ is at the top of the world,

417
00:19:41,375 --> 00:19:43,708
and they invite everyone
to join him there.

418
00:19:43,791 --> 00:19:45,833
An impressive step sequence.

419
00:19:51,916 --> 00:19:54,250
[MOROOKA] Now, his last jump
is one that not even

420
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:57,125
Victor Nikiforov attempted in
the second half of his program.

421
00:19:57,208 --> 00:19:59,166
It's a quadruple Lutz.

422
00:20:01,041 --> 00:20:02,833
[MOROOKA]
He did it!

423
00:20:02,916 --> 00:20:05,875
[JEAN-JACQUES] Nobody else takes
the kind of risks that I do.

424
00:20:05,958 --> 00:20:07,958
I'm the only one
who can handle it.

425
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:11,208
Why? Because I'm the king!

426
00:20:11,291 --> 00:20:14,125
I never stand still.
I never settle.

427
00:20:14,208 --> 00:20:17,666
I wouldn't know how to,
even if I tried!

428
00:20:17,750 --> 00:20:26,125
[AUDIENCE cheers]

429
00:20:26,208 --> 00:20:29,125
[JEAN-JACQUES FANGIRLS cheering]

430
00:20:29,208 --> 00:20:30,333
Huh?

431
00:20:32,250 --> 00:20:34,375
[JEAN-JACQUES FANGIRLS cheering]

432
00:20:34,458 --> 00:20:37,625
That's right--JJ Style!

433
00:20:39,166 --> 00:20:42,166
[MARI] Hey, Yuri, I'm sorry
to call during an event,

434
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:43,666
but Makka got into
the steamed buns,

435
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:45,625
and one of 'em got
stuck in his throat.

436
00:20:45,708 --> 00:20:47,916
Anyway, we're at
the vet right now,

437
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,833
but they're not sure
he's going to make it.

438
00:20:49,916 --> 00:20:54,291
[MOROOKA] Jean-Jacques Leroy's
score is 113.56.


439
00:20:54,375 --> 00:20:57,875
That surpasses his personal
best from Skate Canada!

440
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:01,916
[MARI] I'm sorry.
What do you want us to do?

441
00:21:03,791 --> 00:21:06,916
[YURI] Victor! You need
to get back to Japan.

442
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,750
I can handle the free skate
tomorrow on my own.

443
00:21:11,625 --> 00:21:14,041
Don't eat too many pirozhkis
tomorrow, all right?

444
00:21:14,125 --> 00:21:15,625
Da, da.

445
00:21:16,708 --> 00:21:17,916
[YURI]
You know you have to go back!

446
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,250
I already told you, I can't.

447
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:20,541
[PLISETSKY]
What's with them?

448
00:21:20,625 --> 00:21:21,875
[VICTOR sighs]

449
00:21:24,166 --> 00:21:26,041
[VICTOR]
Yakov!

450
00:21:26,125 --> 00:21:28,208
That's it, thank God!

451
00:21:28,291 --> 00:21:30,875
I'm so glad you're here!
You are the coach for me!

452
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:33,875
What's this?
Crawling back already?

453
00:21:33,958 --> 00:21:35,291
It will just be for tomorrow.

454
00:21:35,375 --> 00:21:37,791
For one day only,
will you be Yuri's coach?

455
00:21:37,875 --> 00:21:38,666
Huh?

456
00:21:38,750 --> 00:21:39,500
Huh?

457
00:21:39,583 --> 00:21:40,833
Huh?

458
00:21:40,916 --> 00:21:44,000
[YURI, YAKOV, PLISETSKY]
Huh?!

459
00:23:17,958 --> 00:23:19,833
[GRANDPA PLISETSKY]
Eat some pirozhkis, Yurochka.

460
00:23:19,916 --> 00:23:20,583
There are plenty.

461
00:23:20,666 --> 00:23:21,750
[YURI]
Can I have one?

462
00:23:21,833 --> 00:23:23,250
[PLISETSKY]
Stay away from my pirozhkis.

463
00:23:23,333 --> 00:23:24,708
[YURI]
You haven't changed, have you?

464
00:23:24,791 --> 00:23:25,958
[PLISETSKY]
Next time, Ninth Skate

465
00:23:26,041 --> 00:23:26,708
[YURI] "Yuri vs...

466
00:23:26,791 --> 00:23:27,708
[PLISETSKY] ...Yuri.

467
00:23:27,791 --> 00:23:29,000
[GRANDPA PLISETSKY]
The Horror!!

468
00:23:29,083 --> 00:23:31,166
[YURI, PLISETSKY]
Rostelecom Cup, Free Skate."

